For some reason, 256 is a weird bitrate. At least on my system, 192 and then 320 play perfectly but any other bitrate sounds low quality O_o

Bitrates should never be trusted. A constant bitrate of 320 is great if the tracks were ripped direct from CD. But what if the original track were already encoded at a lower bitrate, or in a different encoding method? Re-encoding at a higher bitrate will not recover what is already lost, and will actually incur more loss.
